{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: collectors + orchestrator + summary input builder. MOCK-MISS: a unit test of only one parser would miss missing-source wiring bugs. REAL-INFRA: no real network/OS is required because each source client can be in-process fakes returning known payloads. LLM-DEP: behavior checks input payload to generation, not model output quality. MULTI-STEP: no chained agentic pipeline required. Rejected higher levels: 'includes data retrieved from all three sources' is about aggregation completeness before generation, so System/Agentic/Workflow are not required.","test_description":"Wire real aggregation modules with fake source adapters for metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log; execute report build; assert the exact payload passed into the summary-generation interface contains fields from all three sources and source-specific markers/values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when error from one source propagates through aggregator and renderer fallback logic. MOCK-MISS: unit-testing only exception handling in one function can miss cross-module abort behavior. REAL-INFRA: unavailability can be reproduced with an in-process fake source that raises timeout/connection errors; real network outages are not required. LLM-DEP: correctness is fallback behavior, not model quality. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent sequence. Rejected System using behavior text: 'one data source is unavailable' does not require real outage mechanics, only correct degraded report production.","test_description":"Run report pipeline with two fake sources returning valid data and one fake source raising a transport error; assert process completes, exit is non-fatal, output report includes the expected `data unavailable` note in the failed section, and other sections are still populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on semantic faithfulness of generated language to numeric/key input values. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic stubs would always pass and cannot expose hallucination, omission, or value distortion. LLM-DEP: this is directly about generation quality and can vary across real model runs. MULTI-STEP: only one agentic generation step is required, so Workflow is not minimal. Rejected lower levels using behavior text: 'accurately represents the key values' cannot be validated by module wiring alone.","test_description":"Use fixed input datasets with known key values and run the real summary-generation model/API; score output against factuality checks (all required values present, no contradictory numbers, correct trend direction), with repeated runs and acceptance thresholds to account for stochastic variation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary crosses real external systems: source APIs, email transport, and inbox delivery. REAL-INFRA: requires real HTTP/service behavior and real mailbox receipt semantics; in-process mocks can hide auth, TLS, routing, formatting, and provider-side rejection issues. MOCK-HIDE: mocked mail client may pass while real SMTP/API fails. LLM-DEP: behavior is delivery success end-to-end, not generation quality, so Agentic is not required as minimum. MULTI-STEP: not a multi-agent pipeline requirement.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script (or entrypoint) in an environment configured against real test endpoints and a real test mailbox; verify successful run status, confirm email arrival in recipient inbox, and assert subject/body/attachments match expected report format for that run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary risk is coordination between delivery failure handling, persistence, and retry state across runs. MOCK-MISS: unit tests of save/retry helpers miss end-to-end state handoff. REAL-INFRA check: can be caught without real network by forcing mail adapter failure in-process; local filesystem persistence in a temp directory is sufficient at Integration level. LLM-DEP: unrelated to model output quality. MULTI-STEP: two scheduled invocations, but not multiple agentic steps. Rejected System using behavior text: requirement is 'saved to a local file' and 'retried on the next scheduled run', which can be validated by invoking the scheduler entrypoint twice with controlled fakes.","test_description":"Run invocation 1 with fake email adapter returning unreachable error; assert report file is persisted and marked pending. Run invocation 2 (next scheduled execution) with email adapter restored; assert pending report is retried, successfully sent, and local pending artifact is cleared/updated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
